text: Glycosmis decipiens is a species of plant in the family Rutaceae. It is endemic to Peninsular Malaysia. It is threatened by habitat loss. A population is protected in Taman Negara.Chua, L. S. L. 1998. Glycosmis decipiens. 2012 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.
